#EbinMin EbinMax Ein dEinExtrap<200keV  FitRangeForExtrap<200keV DeadTimeDetectors AngularCorr WrapAroundCorrdnubar_beforeCorr dExtrap<200keV dAngularCorr dWA dnubar_afterCorr
#
#
#EbinMin EbinMax : limits of the bin of the incident n energy(MeV)
#Ein : mean value of the incident n energy in the bin (MeV)
#dEin : total absolute uncertainty on the mean incident n energy in the bin (MeV)
#
###Relative bias are defined as :    (corrected_nubar - uncorrected_nubar)/corrected_nubar * 100
#
#Extrap<200keV : relative bias (%) of nubar due to neutron detection thresholds (<200keV) = contribution to nubar of neutrons w/ Eout<200keV
#FitRangeForExtrap<200keV : relative bias  (%) to nubar introduced by the arbitrary choice of the fitting range for the extrapolation of the PFNS below 200keV
#DeadTimeDetectors : relative bias  (%) due to neutron detectors dead-time = contribution to nubar of net amount of lost and mis-identified neutrons due to dead-time
#AngularCorr : relative bias (%) due to limited angular coverage of neutron detectors = conribution to nubar of neutrons emitted where no detector is present
#WrapAroundCorr : relative bias (%) due to neutron emitted in fission induced by slow neutron (wrap-around)
#
#
###The uncertainties listed below are not the uncertainties on the corrections, but are the uncertainties on nubar introduced by accounting for the listed effects
###and they are obtained as : SQRT( (dnubar_corr/nubar_corr)^2 - (dnubar_uncorr/nubar_uncorr)^2) *100
#
#dnubar_beforeCorr : total (sys+stat) relative uncertainty (%) on nubar before corrections listed in this file
#dExtrap<200keV : relative uncertainty (%) on nubar introduced by including the contribution of neutrons w/ Eout<200keV
#dAngularCorr : relative uncertainty (%) on nubar introduced by including the contribution of neutrons emitted where there are no detectors, ie by correcting for the angular distribution of emitted n
#dWA : relative uncertainty (%) on nubar introduced by accounting for neutrons emitted in fission induced by slow neutrons (wrap-around)
#dnubar_afterCorr : total (sys+stat) relative uncertainty (%) on nubar after corrections listed in this file
#
#
#
